    "attributes": {
      "name": "Multi Image Source Field",
      "summary": "The Multi Image Source definition stores an ordered list of images in a single field. Each entry is a full Image Source (direct URL or linked file upload), so it composes with the same per-image data model as the single-image field. Its edit template is a gallery: a hero preview of the highlighted image, a horizontally scrollable thumbnail strip with per-image remove (click a thumbnail to highlight it), a Link Image bar that opens the card chooser (search existing image cards or create a new one), and a compact paste-URL row. Computed outputs mirror the single field: resolvedUrls lists every image's resolved URL in order, and primaryUrl exposes the first as the cover.",
